Cookie files (cookies) are small text files which are used by websites and stored on your computer, tablet or phone. They help you use the website more efficiently.
Cookies are most often used for monitoring user traffic on a website, to save user preferences in terms of language, region or layout of content and individual elements, and to personalise advertising to best suit the user’s preferences. Some cookies are necessary for the proper functioning of our website.
Apart from strictly necessary cookies, we process all other cookies based on your voluntary consent which you can withdraw at any time in the
Cookie Declaration
available on our website. You can also change the settings of the web browsers you use.
