Sub-policy 12
https://www.seb.ee/en/general-principles-processing-personal-data:
General principles for processing personal data
Paragraphs
The core value of AS SEB Pank and the legal persons of the same Group (hereinafter us) is trustworthy customer relations. To offer best services for our customers and to perform all contractual relationships correctly, we collect and preserve your and your related persons’ data in accordance with legal acts.
Starting from 25 May 2018, data protection requirements will be regulated by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). This regulation does not change the general principles of processing personal data, but will add some new rules, such as processing personal data on the basis of legitimate interest, and the obligation of the data controller to inform the Data Protection Inspectorate and the data subject of any security requirement violations that might have occurred during the processing. We process personal data in accordance with the regulation on the basis of the following principles.
We protect the personal data in our possession from unauthorised processing. We collect the personal data pursuant to legislation and we only collect the data necessary to perform the obligations deriving from these legislations and to execute and perform contracts, as well as provide better customer service.
The principles for processing client data are specified in the
SEB Privacy Policy (previously named Terms and conditions for processing personal data at SEB)
.
The principles for processing personal data during recruitment are specified in the
Privacy Policy for Applicants
. Here, we explain which data we process when you apply for a vacant job or internship position, or if you wish to conclude a contract governed by the law of obligations with SEB that grants you access to SEB’s internal IT systems. We also describe which data we process if you obtain such access under a contract concluded with a third party (e.g., if you are an employee of one of our cooperation partners).
The principles for processing data of employees of companies that provide services to us are specified in the
Privacy Policy for Service Provider Employees
. Here, we describe which data we process when you are an employee of a company providing services to SEB and need access to SEB’s premises in order to perform your work duties.
We apply both organisational and technical measures to ensure that personal data is processed safely.
Our employees are familiar with the personal data protection principles and are held accountable if such obligations are violated.
We do not issue personal data to third persons, unless there is a legal basis for issuing the data (e.g. an obligation deriving from the law, we are fulfilling a contractual obligation or the person has consented to issuing the data).
SEB processors of personal data
We reserve the right, with your consent, to send you offers from the companies of SEB Bank Group and from other contractual partners regarding the advertisement of products and services. You have the right to decline the advertising by informing us thereof.
SEB partners
,
SEB car leasing partners
Personal data are preserved in our databases and you have a right to access your personal data at any time. You also have a right to request that your personal data be corrected at any time if the data has changed or is inaccurate for other reasons.
Correct data in our information systems guarantees a smoother and quicker service. You can review your personal data and correct any inaccuracies in our
Internet bank
or by contacting us.
We record all customer orders given to us via all means of communication (e.g. phone, online banking, e-mail) and, if needed, use the recordings to prove and/or reproduce the customer orders.
If you have any questions about data processing, call us at 665 5100, send an e-mail to
andmekaitse@seb.ee
, or contact us via the Internet Bank.
What do we use cookies for?
We use cookies on our website, and we divide them into two categories. Essential cookies are mandatory for the website functioning – they are automatically placed on your device when you visit the website. To provide you with the best possible browsing experience, as well as personalised information about our services, we also use non-essential, i.e., Statistical, Functionality, and Marketing cookies. If you do not agree with the non-essential cookies being used, please select “Accept only essential cookies”.
To learn more, see our
Cookie Policy
.
To review and / or update your cookie preferences, please refer to
cookie settings
.
In addition to Essential cookies which are mandatory for the website functioning, we also use Statistical, Functionality, and Marketing cookies which make it easier for users to browse the webpage, as well as for help us understand the ways in which the website is used.
Cookie is a small text file that consists of letters and numbers, which is saved on your device by the website you visit. It acts as technical support, and facilitates your usage of the website in different ways. Cookies used on our website are placed by SEB, as well as the third parties, and are saved in different ways, depending on the type of the cookie. You can manage your cookie settings below. For more information, please refer to our
Cookie Policy
.
Essential cookies for the Site functions
Allow internet bank user recognition for easier authentication (Functionality cookies)
Statistical cookies
Marketing cookies
Accept cookies
Accept only essential cookies
